summary: People don't see the difference between a confirmed relationship & an unconfirmed one. If people in a relationship are known to...
question: People don't see the difference between a confirmed relationship & an unconfirmed one. If people in a relationship are known to be together, you shouldn't ship them to the extent of discussing sexual positions, but going "they're a good couple, I'm glad they're together" is fine, that's just complimenting a fact. If two people's relationship is unconfirmed (not specifically Dan and Phil, just anyone, who whether they're together or not have not said they are) then it's just pushing 2 people 1/2
answer:
into a corner where it seems like people are saying they’re doing something wrong by not being (openly) together rather than it being a compliment to their relationship. Dan and Phil are best friends, but even if they were together, the fact would still remain their relationship would be unconfirmed. Even if someone believes their together, shipping real people who clearly (even to the people convinced they’re dating) wouldn’t want the public to know, is invasive and constricting. 2/2

/

HMMMmmmmmmmm… yeaaah… 

basically phannies are invasive and obsessive
